This article is a memorandum from President Joe Biden regarding the disclosure of information related to the assassination of President John F. Kennedy. The memorandum states that the United States Government has reviewed its records and made efforts to make classified documents related to the assassination available to the public. The memorandum certifies the continued postponement of public disclosure of certain redacted information in the records, citing the need to protect against identifiable harms to military defense, intelligence operations, law enforcement, and the conduct of foreign relations. The memorandum also mentions the use of Transparency Plans to ensure the eventual release of postponed information. It concludes by authorizing the publication of the memorandum in the Federal Register.